	                                <p>Hey Cristian,</p><p>It's not because of the dependency injection, but because of database relationships between Product and Category, e.g. Product relates to the Category as ManyToOne. So you can get a category of product and, if you have setup inverse side, i.e. OneToMany relationship for the Category - you can get all products of a category. See the <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fknpuniversity.com%2Fscreencast%2Fdoctrine-relations%2Fmany-to-one-relation%3A3yc_Bv8iVgriK9NyUO2KiSQ_U4Y&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://knpuniversity.com/scre...</a> for the real example.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
