	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2762587692" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2762587692" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>hey <a data-dsq-mention="weaverryan:disqus" href="https://disqus.com/by/weaverryan/" rel="nofollow noopener">weaverryan</a> indeed i went with the textfile option! after analizing myself yesterday the code I realized that was the best way to go.</p><p>so indeed, im not using fileType, but textType, and hooking the text-field with a javascript to open the bootstrap modal with the filemanager. and on select, that text-field is filled with the file value.</p><p>the text-field is a read-only file, so the user cant actually interact manually with the name of the file.<br>form is rendered normally.<br>modal</p><p></p><pre><code><br><br>&lt;div class="modal-body"&gt;<br>    &lt;iframe width="100%" height="450" src="{{ asset('vendor/responsive-filemanager/filemanager/dialog.php') }}?type=0&amp;amp;field_id=blog_form_mainImage" frameborder="0" style="overflow: scroll; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: scroll;<br>            "&gt;<br>    &lt;/iframe&gt;<br>&lt;/div&gt;<br></code></pre><p></p><p></p><pre><code><br>//builder stuff<br>-&gt;add('mainImage', TextType::class, [<br>    'attr' =&gt; [<br>        'readonly' =&gt; 'readonly',<br>        'data-target' =&gt; '#browser',<br>        'data-toggle' =&gt; 'modal'<br>    ],<br>    'label' =&gt; 'main_image'<br>])<br></code></pre>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
