	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2758183934">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-06-30</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">Victor Bocharsky</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2758183934" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2758183934" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hey there!</p><p>Yes, you can translate choices directly in your form type using `choice_label` option:<br></p><pre><code>    public function buildForm(FormBuilderInterface $builder, array $options)<br>    {<br>        $builder<br>            // other fields<br>            -&gt;add('isVisible', ChoiceType::class, [<br>                'choices' =&gt; [<br>                    'yes' =&gt; true,<br>                    'no' =&gt; false,<br>                ],<br>                'choice_label' =&gt; function ($value, $key, $index) {<br>                    return 'form.choice.'.$key;<br>                },<br>            ]);<br>    }<br><br></code></pre><p></p><p>For more information about `choice_label` option see <a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fsymfony.com%2Fdoc%2Fcurrent%2Freference%2Fforms%2Ftypes%2Fchoice.html%23choice-label%3Az42b4MFUvNOfrCNWRgFz6AzMxaY&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">ChoiceType Field</a>. And don't forget to enable translator in your config.yml:<br></p><pre><code>framework:<br>    translator: ~<br></code></pre><p></p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
