	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2449682541">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-01-10</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">Bettinz</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2449682541" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2449682541" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Maybe this help someone :) I've solved using a macro</p><p>{% macro purchasedProduct(product) %}<br>&lt;div class="row"&gt;<br>        &lt;div class="col-md-3"&gt;<br>            {{ form_row(<a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fproduct.name%3AG4iPUjDIvT2uW9Qvi0tzH5yiHrs&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">product.name</a>)}}<br>        &lt;/div&gt;<br>    &lt;/div&gt;<br>{% endmacro %}</p><p>and then {% import "form/bootstrap_supplier.html.twig" as supplierForm %}</p><p>and in data-prototype="{{ supplierForm.purchasedProduct(form.products.vars.prototype) |e }}"</p><p>Now I can use col-md-3 for my fields instead the default col-md-10 with a prototype and a collection :)</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
